createTable(Scanner) - Method in class Hash
createTable takes in argument inFile which contains the hashTable text file, reads in each word(adding delims for spaces in case user accidentally adds them to the text file, applies the hash function to each String(word) to get a value from 0 to 36, checks to see if that spot is occupied in the hash table, if it is the occupied variable is incremented and the collision is resolved by chaining via linked lists by added the word to the end of the list.

searchTree(String, PrintWriter) - Method in class Xref
method searchTree() takes in a string s, compares it to Q to make sure the user does not want to quit the program, if not the string is inserted into a new word object and inserted into the tree, the tree invokes searchBST method to find the word and returns a reference to a treeNode, if treeNode is null the program assumes it is not contained in the tree and informs the user, returning to the main program, otherwise the word invokes the visit method in Word, printing the information of the word.
